    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=name: {{ $('Map Lead Fields').item.json.name }}",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "=You are a name extractor. Your task is to normalize a provided name so it can be safely included in an email.\n\n##OUTPUT FORMAT (Strict JSON)\n{\n  \"name\": \"Karim Nabil\"\n}\n\n##INSTRUCTIONS\n\n**Empty input\nIf the provided name is missing, null, or only whitespace → return:\n{ \"name\": \"\" }\nCapitalization\n\n**Always capitalize the first letter of each word in the name.\nExamples:\nkarim → Karim\nkarim nabil → Karim Nabil\naHMeD saLaH → Ahmed Salah\n\n**Company / Department / Generic addresses\nIf the name is one of the following (case-insensitive), return empty:\ninfo, information, marketing, sales, support, admin, team, hr, careers, recruitment, recruiting, jobs,\nhello, contact, enquiries, billing, finance, accounting, customer service, service, help, noreply, no-reply,\nwebmaster, it, ict, office, reception, secretary, gm, ceo, cto, coo, cfo, founder, owner, manager,\ndepartment, dept, operations, ops, social, media, pr, csr\nExample:\nInput: support →\n{ \"name\": \"\" }\n\n##Symbols, emails, or invalid strings\nIf the input contains @, numbers only, or looks like an email/placeholder → return empty.\nExample: support@company.com → { \"name\": \"\" }\n\n##Valid personal names only\nOutput should contain only the cleaned, capitalized personal name."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
